        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 4:27PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 427 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pleasant Valley, or near Virginia City, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pleasant Valley, Damonte Ranch, and Nv 341 At Washoe-Storey Co Line.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
